  <front>
   <head>SONNET [15] XV. From Petrarch.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">WHERE the green leaves exclude the summer beam,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And softly bend as balmy breezes blow,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And where, with liquid lapse, the lucid stream</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Across the fretted rock is heard to flow,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Pensive I lay: When she whom Earth concease,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">As if still living, to my eyes appears,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And pitying Heaven her angel form reveals,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To say — 'Unhappy Petrarch, dry your tears;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">' Ah! Why sad lover! thus before your time,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">'In grief and sadness should your life decay,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">' And like a blighted flow'r, your manly prime</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">'In vain and hopeless sorrow, fade away?</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">' Ah! Yield not thus to culpable despair,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+||-+|-+|-+" line_length="12">'But raise thine eyes to Heav'n — and think I wait thee there.'</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
